abstract: >-
  Management Research Notes is a portable, file-based academic knowledge
  base for management and business sustainability research. Each
  peer-reviewed article becomes one Markdown note with YAML frontmatter
  (trusted bibliographic metadata, a controlled-vocabulary topic taxonomy,
  three custom analytic fields — unit_of_analysis, level_of_theory,
  dependent_variable_family — and verbatim evidence anchors on every
  factual claim) and a human-readable distillation (research question,
  mechanism, theoretical contribution, practical implication, limitations,
  future research, APA citation). A small Python pipeline derives a SQLite
  index with FTS5, a CSV export, and a BibTeX file from the notes, and a
  two-layer faithfulness audit (mechanical substring check on evidence
  anchors plus a cold-context independent auditor scoring prose fields against
  a published rubric) gates every note into the library. Version 0.32.0
  (2026-07-10) adds Academy of Management Journal volume 57, issue 2: 13
  peer-reviewed papers produced under extraction v3 and independently
  audited under rubric v2. Three audit-identified fields were repaired
  from PDF evidence before release: Beckman's board-measure timing,
  Rogan's agency-level robustness qualification, and Wang's
  patent-count-mediated indirect pathway. Fresh re-audits cleared each
  repair; the final issue scan has 117/117 prose-field verdicts SUPPORTED
  with zero PARTIAL, UNSUPPORTED, or CONTRADICTED. All notes validate,
  the manifest lints cleanly, scoped CrossRef matches every changed note,
  and the public SQLite, CSV, and BibTeX indexes contain 1,154 records.
  Earlier, version 0.31.0
  (2026-07-10) adds Academy of Management Journal volume 57, issue 1: 13
  peer-reviewed papers — the first issue produced under extraction v3, so
  every empirical note now records the paper's hypotheses, data and
  measures, and key findings (hypothesis support and effect direction)
  with three additional verbatim evidence anchors, audited under rubric
  v2 across nine prose fields per note. All 13 extractions validated on
  the first attempt and the final audit scan has 117/117 prose-field
  verdicts SUPPORTED with zero PARTIAL, UNSUPPORTED, or CONTRADICTED.
  The release also fixes a references-stripper bug that could truncate
  audit inputs (with regression tests), raises the audit text budget to
  240,000 characters with anchor-aware splicing so the auditor always
  sees the passages backing each claim, migrates the CrossRef
  false-positive registries to JSON data files, and records truthful
  per-run extraction-model provenance (this issue: claude-fable-5).
  Public indexes contain 1,141 records. Earlier, version 0.30.0
  (2026-07-09) is a schema-and-tooling release with no new notes: it
  introduces extraction v3, which adds three empirical body sections to
  every future note — Hypotheses / Propositions, Data & Measures, and Key
  Findings — plus three matching Layer 1 evidence anchors
  (hypotheses_source, measures_overview, findings_overview) and three new
  Layer 2 audited prose fields under audit rubric v2 (nine fields for v3
  notes; a reversed finding direction is CONTRADICTED). The change is
  applied going-forward only: the validator, auditor, and indexer are
  version-gated on extraction_version, all 1,128 existing v1/v2 notes
  revalidate unchanged, and the rebuilt SQLite and CSV indexes carry the
  three new columns with key_findings and hypotheses now searchable via
  FTS5. The release also adds docs/pipeline-runbook.md, a vendor-neutral
  ingest/audit/publish runbook referenced from AGENTS.md, hardens the
  shared CrossRef client used by all three metadata gates with
  retry-with-backoff and negative caching, and fixes stale documentation
  references. Earlier, version 0.29.0
  (2026-07-07) adds Academy of Management Journal volume 58, issues 1-6:
  78 peer-reviewed papers with issue counts 13, 13, 13, 13, 13, and 13. This
  extends AMJ pilot coverage backward to vol. 58 no. 1 through vol. 69 no. 1,
  and the public SQLite, CSV, and BibTeX indexes now contain 1,128 records.
  The AMJ volume-58 release passes the volume validation stack: all AMJ
  volume-58 manifests lint cleanly, all notes validate, scoped CrossRef
  metadata verification for all 78 AMJ volume-58 notes exits 0 with three
  documented CrossRef-side false positives (Byron title inline-HTML spacing,
  Little / Smith Major author parsing, and Joshi title inline-HTML spacing),
  and the full library has 1,128/1,128 PASS, 0 UNSUPPORTED, and
  0 CONTRADICTED audit verdicts. The final AMJ volume-58 audit scan has
  468/468 prose-field verdicts SUPPORTED after six audit-identified prose
  fields were narrowed before release. Earlier, version 0.28.0 (2026-07-05)
  adds Academy of Management Journal volume 59, issues 1-6: 95 peer-reviewed
  papers with issue counts 16, 15, 16, 16, 16, and 16. This extends AMJ pilot
  coverage backward to vol. 59 no. 1 through vol. 69 no. 1, and the public
  SQLite, CSV, and BibTeX indexes now contain 1,050 records. The AMJ
  volume-59 release passes the volume validation stack: all AMJ volume-59
  manifests lint cleanly, all notes validate, scoped CrossRef metadata
  verification for all 95 AMJ volume-59 notes exits 0 with two documented
  CrossRef-side title false positives in issue 1 (Durand and Zavyalova
  malformed inline HTML), and the full library has 1,050/1,050 PASS,
  0 UNSUPPORTED, and 0 CONTRADICTED audit verdicts. The final AMJ volume-59
  audit scan has 570/570 prose-field verdicts SUPPORTED. Earlier,
  version 0.27.0 (2026-07-03) adds Academy of Management Journal volume 60,
  issues 1-6: 95 peer-reviewed papers with issue counts 16, 16, 16, 17, 15,
  and 15. This extends AMJ pilot coverage backward to vol. 60 no. 1 through
  vol. 69 no. 1, and the public SQLite, CSV, and BibTeX indexes now contain
  955 records.
  The AMJ volume-60 release passes the volume validation stack: all AMJ
  volume-60 manifests lint cleanly, all notes validate, scoped CrossRef
  metadata verification for all 95 AMJ volume-60 notes exits 0 with no
  mismatches, two AMJ volume-60 author-name notices are documented as
  CrossRef-side family-name parsing false positives, and the full library has
  955/955 PASS, 0 UNSUPPORTED, and 0 CONTRADICTED audit verdicts. The final
  AMJ volume-60 audit scan has 570/570 prose-field verdicts SUPPORTED after
  two audit-identified future-research fields were narrowed before release.
  Earlier, version 0.26.0
  (2026-07-02) adds Academy of Management Journal volume 61, issues 1-6:
  93 peer-reviewed papers with issue counts 16, 16, 15, 15, 16, and 15. This
  extends AMJ pilot coverage backward to vol. 61 no. 1 through vol. 69 no. 1,
  and the public SQLite, CSV, and BibTeX indexes now contain 860 records.
  The AMJ volume-61 release passes the volume validation stack: all AMJ
  volume-61 manifests lint cleanly, all notes validate, scoped CrossRef
  metadata verification for all 93 AMJ volume-61 notes exits 0 with no
  mismatches, and the full library has 860/860 PASS, 0 UNSUPPORTED, and
  0 CONTRADICTED audit verdicts. Earlier, version 0.25.0
  (2026-06-30) adds Academy of Management Journal volume 62, issues 1-6:
  76 peer-reviewed papers with issue counts 12, 12, 13, 13, 12, and 14. This
  extends AMJ pilot coverage backward to vol. 62 no. 1 through vol. 69 no. 1,
  and the public SQLite, CSV, and BibTeX indexes now contain 767 records.
  The AMJ volume-62 release passes the volume validation stack: all AMJ
  volume-62 manifests lint cleanly, all notes validate, scoped CrossRef
  metadata verification for all 76 AMJ volume-62 notes exits 0 with no
  mismatches, and the full library has 767/767 PASS, 0 UNSUPPORTED, and
  0 CONTRADICTED audit verdicts. The full-library CrossRef sweep was attempted
  during release preparation but interrupted by a network-level HTTPS
  handshake stall; existing pre-AMJ62 notes were unchanged from the v0.24.0
  metadata-verified snapshot. Earlier, version 0.24.0
  (2026-06-28) adds Academy of Management Journal volume 63, issues 1-6:
  74 peer-reviewed papers with issue counts 13, 12, 12, 12, 12, and 13. This
  extends AMJ pilot coverage backward to vol. 63 no. 1 through vol. 69 no. 1,
  and the public SQLite, CSV, and BibTeX indexes now contain 691 records.
  The release passes the full validation stack: all AMJ volume-63 manifests
  lint cleanly, all notes validate, CrossRef metadata verification exits 0
  with no mismatches; remaining notices are documented CrossRef-side false
  positives or lookup warnings, and the full library has 691/691 PASS,
  0 UNSUPPORTED, and 0 CONTRADICTED audit verdicts. Earlier, version 0.23.1
  (2026-06-27) was a provenance-focused patch over v0.23.0: the 75 Academy of
  Management Journal volume-64 notes now record extraction_model "gpt-5.5"
  instead of the stale bundle value "claude-opus-4-8", and five
  audit-identified wording issues were narrowed: Abdurakhmonov et al. (2021)
  removed an overbroad country-generalization phrase, Jacobs et al. (2021)
  softened a direct practical prescription to a case-grounded association,
  Lifshitz-Assaf et al. (2021) removed an unsupported stage-gate reference,
  Bain et al. (2021) distinguished experimental boundary tests from the Study 3
  intervention target, and Ji et al. (2021) removed an unstated
  national/historical-setting limitation. Version 0.23.0 (2026-06-27) added
  Academy of Management
  Journal volume 64, issues 1-6: 75
  peer-reviewed papers with issue counts 12, 12, 13, 12, 13, and 13. This
  completes AMJ pilot coverage from vol. 64 no. 1 through vol.
  69 no. 1, and the public SQLite, CSV, and BibTeX indexes now contain 617
  records. The release passes the full validation stack: all AMJ volume-64
  manifests lint cleanly, all notes validate, CrossRef metadata verification
  exits 0 with no mismatches; remaining notices are documented CrossRef-side
  false positives or lookup warnings, and the full library has 617/617 PASS,
  0 UNSUPPORTED, and 0 CONTRADICTED audit
  verdicts. Earlier, version 0.22.0 (2026-06-24) added Academy of Management
  Journal volume 65, issues 1-6: 77 peer-reviewed papers with issue counts
  13, 13, 13, 12, 13, and 13. Earlier, version
  0.21.0 (2026-06-23) added the Network for Business Sustainability (NBS)
  January 2026 monthly digest: 113 peer-reviewed papers led by the Journal
  of Business Ethics (40) with Research Policy, the Journal of
  Environmental Economics and Management, Organization Science, Human
  Relations, The Journal of Finance, MIS Quarterly, and other journals, all
  passing the two-layer faithfulness audit. Each batch ran as two small
  extraction waves through the pipeline() workflow to stay under a transient
  server rate-limit while keeping the subagent count code-guaranteed, and
  the batch surfaced further SSRN working papers that had reached their
  published journal version (upgraded to the journal DOI and metadata).
  Earlier, version 0.20.0 (2026-06-11) added the Network for Business
  Sustainability (NBS) December 2025 monthly digest: 82 peer-reviewed
  papers spanning Ecological Economics (including the biodiversity-and-
  finance special issue), the Academy of Management Journal, Business &
  Society, Review of Finance, Strategic Management Journal, and other
  journals, all passing the two-layer faithfulness audit. The batch
  introduced masthead-based detection of SSRN working papers that had
  reached their published journal version (upgrading them to the journal
  DOI and bibliographic metadata) and a code-orchestrated parallel-
  dispatch extraction workflow that guarantees the subagent count.
  Earlier, version 0.19.1
  (2026-05-27) is a provenance-correction patch over v0.19.0: no new
  notes; the extraction_model field was corrected from claude-opus-4-6
  (the bundle's stale default that v0.18.0 had standardized into 108
  notes) to claude-opus-4-7 for all notes ingested on or after
  2026-04-18 — the earliest date with direct agent self-report evidence
  of Opus 4.7 use. 105 pre-cutover notes retain claude-opus-4-6 as
  historical record. tools/prepare_paper.py constant updated so future
  bundles record the accurate model. v0.19.0 (2026-05-23) added AMJ
  vol-66-no-1 (13 notes: Carton, Chan, Cudennec, Dimotakis, Dwertmann,
  Gruber editorial, Kundro, Lauriano, Leppänen, Lockwood, Neuberger,
  Ong, Xu) and served as the standalone validation of the
  extraction_model verbatim fix in docs/extraction-prompt.md; 13/13
  Layer 1 first-try PASS, 13/13 Layer 2 PASS with 0 PARTIAL — the third
  perfectly-clean batch. The current v0.32.0 snapshot contains 1,154 curated
  notes: 272 from the Network for Business Sustainability monthly digests
  and 882 AMJ pilot notes across vol. 57 no. 1-2 plus vol. 58 no. 1 through
  vol. 69 no. 1. Both vol-57 v3 issues pass at 117/117 prose-field verdicts
  SUPPORTED; the full library has 1,154/1,154 PASS and zero UNSUPPORTED or
  CONTRADICTED verdicts. An AGENTS.md file provides
  a tool-agnostic
  entry point so that AI agents (Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, custom
  SDK apps) can discover and consume the data with known faithfulness
  guarantees.
